3. Implemented the solution in `web/src/services/clients/web-api-client.ts`:

```typescript
Axios.interceptors.response.use(
  async (response) => {
    // 成功レスポンスの場合、403 エラー状態をクリア
    if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
      const { getGlobalAccessDeniedSetter } = await import(
        '@/contexts/access-denied.context'
      );
      const setter = getGlobalAccessDeniedSetter();
      if (setter) {
        setter(false);
      }
    }
    return response;
  },
  async (error) => {
    // 403 Forbidden エラーの場合、グローバル状態を更新
    if (error?.response?.status === 403) {
      if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
        const { getGlobalAccessDeniedSetter } = await import(
          '@/contexts/access-denied.context'
        );
        const setter = getGlobalAccessDeniedSetter();
        if (setter) {
          setter(true);
        }
      }
    }
    return Promise.reject(error);
  },
);
```

**Reasoning Provided**:
- More accurate state management based on API success/failure
- Handles same-page scenarios (e.g., filter changes with same URL where `router.pathname` doesn't change)
- Similar to Flutter's Dio interceptor pattern
- The page navigation reset (in ConsoleLayout) remains as a failsafe

